aVPolice are searching for a missing, pregnant Maryland teacher after she didn\u2019t show up for the first day of school Tuesday.\u000a\u000aLaura Elizabeth Wallen, 31, has not been heard from since Sunday, when she sent a text message to family members that police called \u201ctroubling,\u201d Fox 5 reported. The content of the text message has not been released.\u000a\u000aPolice are concerned for both Wallen\u2019s physical and emotional welfare. She is believed to be at least three months pregnant.\u000a\u000aMontgomery County police are asking for help from the community to find Wallen, who lives in Olney and teaches social studies at Wilde Lake High School, Fox 5 reported. She may be driving a black 2011 Ford Escape.\u000a\u000aThe high school has provided counseling for students, who have been informed of Wallen\u2019s disappearance by their homeroom teachers, Fox 5 reported.\u000a\u000a\u201cShe was a favorite amongst the students,\u201d Paris Cooper, who is a student, said, CBS News reported. \u201cShe was really nice and this is really sad, what\u2019s happening, you see it\u2019s really taking a toll on people.\u201d\u000a\u000aFamily members reported Wallen was excited about her pregnancy and did not appear troubled. She left her dog behind when she disappeared, CBS News reported.\u000a\u000a\u201cI\u2019m hoping they find her and I\u2019m hoping that she\u2019ll be alive and well,\u201d neighbor Joyce Robinson said, CBS News reported.\u000a\u000aWallen had spent many hours over several days preparing her classroom for the first day of school before disappearing. \u201cPeople are concerned for her safety,\u201d Brian Bassett of Howard County Schools said, CBS reported.\u000a\u000aMany students posted on social media about Wallen\u2019s disappearance.\u000a\u000aThinking of Ms. Wallen every night, breaks my heart. She motivated me even on my worse days. #bringwallenhome \u2014 Natalie (@nataweenie) September 8, 2017\u000a\u000aDon't forget to put a note on Ms.Wallen's door to show how much we miss & appreciate her#BringWallenHome \u2014 WLHS CLASS OF 2018 (@wildelake2018) September 6, 2017\u000a\u000a#BringWallenHome\u000a\u000aI literally check the news 5 times a day hoping too see she's home \U0001f614 \u2014 ceci (@tworkaholic) September 7, 2017
