aVPresident Donald Trump sent tweets on a number of topics Friday morning, including a criticism of Republicans for their attempts to repeal and replace Obamacare that "didn\u2019t happen."\u000a\u000aRepublicans, sorry, but I've been hearing about Repeal & Replace for 7 years, didn't happen! Even worse, the Senate Filibuster Rule will.... \u2014 Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) September 8, 2017\u000a\u000aThe president also blamed the filibuster rule in the Senate for the lack of success on repealing Obamacare, calling the rule a \u201cdeath wish\u201d for Republicans.\u000a\u000a...never allow the Republicans to pass even great legislation. 8 Dems control - will rarely get 60 (vs. 51) votes. It is a Repub Death Wish! \u2014 Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) September 8, 2017\u000a\u000aThen the president urged Republicans to get to work on tax reform legislation.\u000a\u000aRepublicans must start the Tax Reform/Tax Cut legislation ASAP. Don't wait until the end of September. Needed now more than ever. Hurry! \u2014 Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) September 8, 2017\u000a\u000aThe president appeared to show this week that he is more willing to work with Democrats, after striking a deal on the debt ceiling with Democratic leaders.
