aVThe response by the Trump administration to Hurricane Harvey "has been amazing," Eric Trump told Newsmax TV on Tuesday.\u000a\u000a"You saw how quickly, even before the storm hit, they declared it an emergency," President Donald Trump's son told "The Joe Pags Show" in an exclusive interview. "They started getting all the assets down there.\u000a\u000a"The coordination with the state and local governments have been phenomenal."\u000a\u000aImportant: Newsmax TV is available on DirecTV Ch. 349, U-Verse 1220, and FiOS 615. If your cable operator does not have Newsmax TV just call and ask them to put us on \u2013 Call toll-free 1-844-500-6397 and we will connect you right away to your cable operator!\u000a\u000aFor more places to Find Newsmax TV \u2013 Click Here Now\u000a\u000aPresident Trump vowed Tuesday that his administration's response to the devastation caused by Harvey would be "better than ever before."\u000a\u000aEric Trump especially praised the "Cajun Navy" and other volunteers who rescued stranded residents with their own boats and other water vehicles.\u000a\u000a"More impressive than anything you see kind of \u2014 what are they calling it, the Cajun Navy? \u2014 but you see great Americans going out in force to help others in need.\u000a\u000a"They're dropping everything and leaving their own and their own families to go rescue people," he added. "There's nothing worse than this.\u000a\u000a"It's just the spirit of the people down there has actually been incredibly uplifting, especially in light of so much of the nonsense that we see on the streets every single day."
