aVThe daughter of former Vice President Joe Biden said she is hopeful that her father will run for president in 2020.\u000a\u000a"I hope so," said Ashley Biden, a fashion designer, in a Women's Wear Daily interview posted Thursday.\u000a\u000a"He's busier truly than ever \u2026 he'll make the decision when the time comes," Biden said.\u000a\u000aHer father has plenty of time to make the decision, she said.\u000a\u000a"It's a little ways away. A lot can happen and we know this as a family. If he is in good health, knock on wood, and seeing what the landscape is at the time, yeah, I think he is considering it.\u000a\u000a"The man is sort of supercharged. So I think, if we get to that point, yeah, I think he will do it," she said.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aBiden said she told her father that he could run for one term.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a"I only tell him four years \u2014 I'm like, 'Listen, this is the deal. If you do it, four years and then we're out,'" she said.
