aVWhy do some option trades win or lose?\u000a\u000aAn Austin based trading education firm just released the results of an option trading case study. Starting in January, 2017, John Carter of Simpler Trading placed real-money trades in his account. To date, these positions generated over 98% returns on individual stock options.\u000a\u000aSome were surprised that the rapid account growth did not rely on the market hitting new all-time highs. In fact, John selected stocks that moved independently from the broad market.\u000a\u000aAre you an active stock or option trader? Then you know how frustrating it can be when you\u2019re correct about a stock\u2019s direction but still lose on the trade. According to John Carter\u2019s case study, careful option strategy selection can improve odds of profitability.\u000a\u000aIn addition, the odds of consistent returns and rapid growth may be increased when low probability setups are filtered out. Because of how the value of an option fluctuates, John Carter strives to identify special situations when a greater than expected move is probable.\u000a\u000aJohn Carter has more than 25 years trading experience and has authored several books on his methods. If you would like to know more about the strategies that generated over 98% returns since January 2017, attend Simpler Trading\u2019s upcoming free webinar on rapid account growth.\u000a\u000aRegister for the Case Study Webinar
