aVConservative commentator Michelle Malkin said Friday that President Donald Trump shouldn't be criticized for working with Democrats to raise the debt ceiling.\u000a\u000a"You have to deal with crap-weasels to your left and crap-weasels to your right," she said on Fox News, agreeing with Rep. Jim Jordan, R-Ohio, who said that Trump has no good options to deal with the Washington, D.C. "swamp."\u000a\u000aShe added that Republican leaders Paul Ryan and Mitch McConnell "rendered themselves irrelevant and obsolete a long time ago."\u000a\u000aOn Thursday, Malkin appeared on Fox Business Network, where she told host Lou Dobbs that 'Dreamers,' those who were granted amnesty under the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program, "deserve nothing."\u000a\u000a"The fact is that if there were a single 'deserving dreamer' in this country, they would be deserving because they would acknowledge that they are owed nothing and that they deserve nothing from a country into which they were born because of their parents' illegal activity," she said, according to Media Matters.\u000a\u000aThe Trump administration announced recently that the program will end in six months, though the president did voice support for congressional legislation that would replace it.\u000a\u000a"You can talk to anyone who's come into the country the right and proper way, including my own parents," Malkin continued. "There are so many first- and second- generation Americans who understand that citizenship is a privilege and not a right. And when you have an entire class of 800,000 people who feel entitled to be here despite the law, you are creating the very trouble we are in now."
