aVFormer Colorado Rep. Tom Tancredo on Wednesday said Donald Trump was right in terminating DACA, and Congress might unify and pass a bill to provide the "Dreamers" amnesty because of how much hatred they have for the president.\u000a\u000a"It is not President Trump's fault; it is absolutely what he should have done," Tancredo told hosts Bill Tucker and Carl Roth on NewsmaxTV's "Newsmax Now."\u000a\u000a". . . A lot of people think it's actually a law somehow, and Trump is repealing it somehow by executive order. No, not the way it happened at all, of course. Here are the exact words Barack Obama in the Rose Garden when he announced this executive action: 'Let's be clear, this is not amnesty, this is not immunity, this is not a path to citizenship, it is not a permanent fix, it is a temporary stopgap measure that lets us focus our resources,' and it is of course completely unconstitutional \u2013 oh no wait, that's not right."\u000a\u000aImportant: Newsmax TV is available on DirecTV Ch. 349, U-Verse 1220, and FiOS 615. If your cable operator does not have Newsmax TV just call and ask them to put us on \u2013 Call toll-free 1-844-500-6397 and we will connect you right away to your cable operator!\u000a\u000aFor more places to Find Newsmax TV \u2013 Click Here Now\u000a\u000aThe Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program started in 2012 under Obama via an executive order. Trump during the campaign spoke many times about his desire to end the program, which grants amnesty to undocumented immigrants who entered the United States as children.\u000a\u000aAttorney General Jeff Sessions on Tuesday announced Trump's decision to end DACA with a six-month delay, giving Congress a window to act.\u000a\u000aTancredo said he thinks it is "very possible" Congress will come together.\u000a\u000a"All of the same division in Congress that has stopped it from doing anything all these years are still there, but the only difference is Donald Trump, and they hate him more than anything else," he said.
