aVConservative firebrand Ann Coulter is pretty much on the money when she says President Donald Trump should skip tax reform for now and focus on building a U.S.-Mexico border wall and deporting illegal immigrants, former Rep. Michael Patrick Flanagan told Newsmax TV on Thursday.\u000a\u000a"Ann ignores the fact we're trying to lower the tax on businesses \u2014 we haven't done that in ages and that's really an important task \u2014 but Ann is right," Flanagan, now president of Flanagan Consulting LLC, a Washington, D.C., lobbying firm, said to Newsmax's JD Hayworth.\u000a\u000aImportant: Newsmax TV is available on DirecTV Ch. 349, U-verse 1220, and FiOS 615. If your cable operator doesn't have Newsmax TV just call and ask them to put us on \u2014 Call toll-free 1-844-500-6397 and we'll connect you right away to your cable operator!\u000a\u000aFor more places to Find Newsmax TV \u2014 Click Here Now\u000a\u000a"We can't lose our focus on the wall, on healthcare, getting rid of Obamacare and taxes, but they're in interrelated and this is the complication of it. This is what Washingtonians have to communicate.\u000a\u000a"And if Paul Ryan were running the House under regular order, if we actually had a Congress communicating these concepts \u2014 that they're all interrelated, that we have to move them all more or less together \u2014 the American people would understand this better than us."\u000a\u000aOn Wednesday, Coulter ripped Trump as he made a speech on his tax reform plan in Springfield, Missouri.\u000a\u000aIn a long string of tweets, Coulter said Trump should focus instead on building a border wall to keep out illegal immigrants and deporting those already here.\u000a\u000aWTF! Why is @realDonaldTrump back to tax cuts? His election was NOT about tax cuts. Has he been talking to @SpeakerRyan again? \u2014 Ann Coulter (@AnnCoulter) August 30, 2017\u000a\u000aThis isn't a "once in a lifetime" shot at tax cuts! EVERY GOP cuts taxes! This is "once in a lifetime" shot to save US: Wall & deportations! \u2014 Ann Coulter (@AnnCoulter) August 30, 2017\u000a\u000aBush cut taxes! Did it create millions of jobs? Nope. The rich pocketed their tax cut & sent jobs abroad, hired guest workers. F-- them. \u2014 Ann Coulter (@AnnCoulter) August 30, 2017\u000a\u000aIt's so obvious Trump's only getting polite applause for tax cuts. Want to get the crowd hollering, @realDonaldTrump? Talk about THE WALL! \u2014 Ann Coulter (@AnnCoulter) August 30, 2017\u000a\u000aIt's like Night of the Living Dead watching our beloved @realDonaldTrump go to DC & start babbling the same old GOP nonsense on tax cuts. \u2014 Ann Coulter (@AnnCoulter) August 30, 2017\u000a\u000aTax cuts are a 2d term issue. 1st term: BUILD THE WALL, End DACA, Deport Illegals, No Refugees, No Muslims, Immigrn Moratorium. SAVE USA! \u2014 Ann Coulter (@AnnCoulter) August 30, 2017\u000a\u000aThis is the worst, most tone-deaf speech @realDonaldTrump has ever given. Jeb! had better ideas. \u2014 Ann Coulter (@AnnCoulter) August 30, 2017\u000a\u000aOh stop pretending this is about letting "families" keep more of their money. HALF OF AMERICANS DON'T PAY TAXES! This is for Wall Street. \u2014 Ann Coulter (@AnnCoulter) August 30, 2017\u000a\u000aUnder what theory of the constitution does the COMMANDER IN CHIEF have authority to build a wall in Syria, but not on our own border? https://t.co/Td88gCvBxG \u2014 Ann Coulter (@AnnCoulter) August 30, 2017\u000a\u000aNot tax cuts? Weird. https://t.co/NePTeI4UyS \u2014 Ann Coulter (@AnnCoulter) August 30, 2017\u000a\u000aFlanagan, who served Illinois's 5th District from 1995 to 1997, said Republican-controlled Washington seems to "hopscotch from one issue to the next, to the next and leaving behind important ones and embracing new ones."\u000a\u000aBut that could change now that four 2018 Republican congressional candidates in Minnesota who are challenging Democratic incumbents are declining to support Ryan's leadership, Flanagan told Hayworth.\u000a\u000a"They just form a center of gravity to pull the party left or right. It's the guys in the middle, if you can get them to revolt, or to say 'look, Mr. Speaker, we're not playing anymore until you fix this.' That's when change begins to happen," Flanagan said.\u000a\u000aThose four candidates, according to The Washington Post, are: St. Louis County Commissioner Pete Stauber, challenging Democratic Rep. Rick Nolan; commercial pilot Dave Hughes, taking on Rep. Collin Peterson; state Rep. Tim Miller, also challenging Peterson; and businessman Jim Hagedorn, running for the seat to be vacated by Rep. Tim Walz.
