tial candidacies in 2008 and 2012.\u2014 The "Die Hard" star denies the label "Republican," claiming to dislike both parties, but opposes gun control and has spoken out to support the Bill of Rights.\u2014 The "Saturday Night Live" comic is a registered Republican and donated $2,100 to Rudy Giuliani's campaign for president. He also performed at the 2004 Republican Convention.\u2014 The "Nutty Professor" and longtime host of the Muscular Dystrophy Association Labor Day Telethon has blasted Obama for his failures in combating ISIS and has praised both Donald Trump and Ronald Reagan.\u2014 The tough guy star of "Walker, Texas Ranger" and martial arts movie fame is a committed Christian who supported GOP candidate Mike Huckabee in 2008 and regularly writes conservative columns for World Net Daily.\u2014 After appearing in 1979's "The Champ," Schroder went on to become a child star on TV's "Silver Spoons." A self-described "patriot to the core," Schroder spoke at the 2000 Republican National Convention in support of George W. Bush and also backed John McCain in 2008.\u2014 A registered Republican, the former "Happy Days" and "Charles in Charge" star once campaigned for Ronald Reagan and has spoken out on social media about his political beliefs. He recently endorsed Donald Trump for president.\u2014 The African-American "Clueless" star supported Mitt Romney over Obama and has been a Fox News contributor.\u2014 The rapper and actor, whose real name is James Todd Smith, is a very vocal conservative and has performed at the Republican National Convention.\u2014 The legendary country singer and "Coal Miner's Daughter" recently announced that she is supporting Donald Trump for president and has said she is willing to campaign for him.\u2014 The moniker replaces his real name of Robert James Ritchie, but nothing can replace the Republican Party in the singer/rapper's view. He has made many overseas tours to entertain American troops, and allowed the Romney campaign free use of his songs when Mitt ran for president. This campaign cycle, he endorsed Ben Carson and, later, Donald Trump.\u2014 The longtime star of the TV soap "All My Children" and Emmy winner is a well-known conservative Republican.\u2014 The one-time "teen idol" and longtime singing star is a conservative, Republican Christian who received a lifetime achievement award from the Conservative Political Action Conference.\u2014The shock rocker, whose real name is Vincent Damon Furnier, issurprisingly a hardcore born-again Christian conservative with strong Creationist beliefs.\u2014 The actor, producer, author, director, and star of "Threesome," "The Flintstones in Viva Rock Vegas," and "Celebrity Apprentice" is a born-again Christian who backed Mike Huckabee for president.\u2014 The smiling host of "Wheel of Fortune" is an outspoken conservative who has challenged global warming theorists, written for the conservative magazine Human Events, and donated to Republican candidates.\u2014 The "Bat Out of Hell" rock-opera singer, "The Rocky Horror Picture Show" actor, and TV host endorsed Mitt Romney for president and has blasted the removal of prayer from public schools.\u2014 The star of "Do The Right Thing," "The Godfather Part II," and "The Last Don" is a conservative Republican who favors Ted Cruz in the current presidential race.\u2014 The actress, singer, reality television personality, and clothing designer is a registered Republican who endorsed George Bush for president in 2004 and has made numerous trips overseas to entertain American troops.
