aVAn easy way to go beyond the guidelines is to get in the habit of an occasional fast.\u000a\u000aFasting is beneficial for weight loss because going without food for even a day immediately lessens the amount of calories you\u2019ll be taking in over the long term.\u000a\u000aBut there\u2019s more to it than just saving calories. Going on a fast sends a signal of semi-starvation that puts the whole body on alert. It then starts using stored fat, drawing it out of your blood and other places.\u000a\u000aSo fats stored in the blood, like cholesterol and triglycerides, begin to disappear.\u000a\u000aFasting also cleanses the body, and gives organs a break from constantly metabolizing food. As a result, immunologic response improves, blood pressure goes down, and people report feeling more clear-headed
