aVKid Rock slammed Nazis and the Ku Klux Klan during a concert in his home state of Michigan Wednesday night.\u000a\u000a"If you want to take a knee or sit during our 'Star-Spangled Banner,' call me a racist because I'm not PC and think you have to remind me that black lives matter. Nazis, ******* bigots and now again the KKK, screw all you ******** stay the **** away," Kid Rock said during the concert, according to MLive.\u000a\u000a"If 'Kid Rock for Senate' has got folks in disarray, wait 'til they hear 'Kid Rock for President of the U.S.A.'," he added.\u000a\u000aKid Rock, has been promoting the possibility that he will run for Senate in Michigan against Sen. Debbie Stabenow, D-Mich. The rock star's merchandise includes t-shirts and hats with the slogan "Kid Rock for Senate."\u000a\u000aOn Sept. 1, a watchdog group said that Kid Rock's possible Senate run could be a violation of campaign finance law, according to The Hill.\u000a\u000a"I am starting to see reports from the misinformed press and the fake news on how I am in violation of breaking campaign law. #1, I have not officially announced my candidacy. #2, See #1 and go **** yourselves," Kid Rock commented in a post on his website.
